does anyone know the statute of limitations in illinois and ohio i am recieving calls from a collection agency in ohio the debt is years old they called me weeks ago and i have yet to recieve anything in writing from them they called me today and i stated i have still not recieved a letter from them and they told me to become a man and pay my bills and to stop stalling by waiting on a letter please help the link that the first poster shows an incorrect sol for open oral accounts in ohio the sol for open accounts is years not you did not mention what type of debt it is if it is a credit card ohio code excludes credit cards as written accounts the collector has violated a usc g of the fdcpa and possibly other violations as well a within five days after the initial communication with a consumer in connection with the collection of any debt a debt collector shall unless the following information is contained in the initial communication or the consumer has paid the debt send the consumer a written notice containing http www ftc gov os statutes fdcpa fdcpact htm if the first time you have heard from this collection agency was by that phone call weeks ago send them a debt validation letter before days has passed from that contact do not sign your name to the letter only print your initials or type your name send it certified mail return receipt they must cease all collection activities until they validate which could include selling the account to another collector if it has been that long since you defaulted they cannot legally place it on your credit report if you are past the collecting sol after they validate or days have passed since they signed the green certified card send them a sol letter a correctly worded sol letter will keep them from contacting you again if you are past sol and inform them of that fact they will probably not sue since the judge would not look favorably on them for filing suit on a debt they know is time barred you might click on the last link i have listed in my profile do some reading in the credit forum edit while some states allow the collecting sol to be re set if a payment is made after the account is charged off it is generally when a written agreement is made before or at the time of payment i would not recommend sending a full cease desist without including the fact the account is time barred i wouldn't send either a sol letter or a c d as your first letter i would recommend that you send a validation letter if you are still within the first days from their first contact it will keep them in validation which would legally tie their hands until they provide proper validation after years it is unlikely but not impossible for them to be able to provide validation United States Postal Service Credit card Plame affair Article One of the United States Constitution Contract E-mail spam Gmail Copyright Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Mail Appeal 2004 U.S. election voting controversies, Ohio Online Copyright Infringement Liability Limitation Act Tom DeLay Medical prescription Internet fraud Washington gubernatorial election, 2004 Annuity 2004 U.S. presidential election controversy and irregularities Postage stamp Phishing Password Trademark 2004 U.S. presidential election controversy, vote suppression Bush v. Gore Mortgage Public domain GNU General Public License Kazaa Data retention Credit repair Public-key cryptography International Criminal Court Child support Euro Social Security (United States) HTML Octopus card Opera (web browser) Spam (electronic) Schabir Shaik Trial Killian documents SCO-Linux controversies Morse Code Apple Computer E-mail Debt Surveillance Tax protester Probation officer America Online Supreme Court of the United States Legal research Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Domain Name System Microeconomics Pretty Good Privacy Stopping e-mail abuse Domestic partnerships in California Mensal__o scandal CAN-SPAM Act of 2003 Credit score Student loan Bank 2003 